WEBVTT

1
00:00:21.906 --> 00:00:23.755
Good news. everyone!

2
00:00:27.878 --> 00:00:29.278
Well? What is it?

3
00:00:29.346 --> 00:00:30.646
What is what?

4
00:00:30.714 --> 00:00:33.298
Oh. right!
Ladies and gentlemen.

5
00:00:33.367 --> 00:00:37.736
We'll be delivering
this mysterious crate
to Peebles Alpha.

6
00:00:37.788 --> 00:00:38.920
Peebles Alpha?

7
00:00:38.989 --> 00:00:41.523
The planet of gangs.
thugs and hustlers?

8
00:00:41.592 --> 00:00:43.286
Ooh! Let's go!
Let's go! Let's go!

9
00:00:43.310 --> 00:00:46.039
Hang on.
If we're delivering
a package to criminals.

10
00:00:46.063 --> 00:00:47.407
I want to know what's in it.

11
00:00:47.431 --> 00:00:49.665
I have no idea. Leela.

12
00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:52.500
But I'll tell you
the same thing
they told me.

13
00:00:52.586 --> 00:00:54.419
"Stop asking questions. old man.

14
00:00:54.488 --> 00:00:56.421
"and we'll slip you
an extra five grand

15
00:00:56.490 --> 00:00:59.357
"that your crew doesn't
need to know about."

16
00:01:02.012 --> 00:01:03.589
Now. listen carefully.

17
00:01:03.613 --> 00:01:06.564
This planet is controlled
by two rival gangs.

18
00:01:06.633 --> 00:01:08.500
the Blips and the Cruds.

19
00:01:08.569 --> 00:01:12.420
You can tell them
apart by their colors.
red and blue.

20
00:01:12.490 --> 00:01:14.739
Which gang's red.
and which gang's blue?

21
00:01:14.808 --> 00:01:16.175
Both!

22
00:01:16.243 --> 00:01:18.310
The delivery is
going to the Blips.

23
00:01:18.379 --> 00:01:22.281
So when you meet them.
you'll want to be wearing
these jerseys.

24
00:01:22.349 --> 00:01:24.283
Not these jerseys.

25
00:01:24.351 --> 00:01:27.536
'Cause if you're wearing
these. you'll be killed
on the spot.

26
00:01:27.605 --> 00:01:29.965
Okay. here are your jerseys.

27
00:01:30.207 --> 00:01:32.073
No. wait. Here.

28
00:01:32.877 --> 00:01:34.409
No. Wait...

29
00:01:42.603 --> 00:01:44.970
Does anyone else find
this delivery suspicious?

30
00:01:45.038 --> 00:01:47.906
Nope. He's too dumb
and I don't care.

31
00:01:47.975 --> 00:01:50.308
Well. I'm smart
and I care too much.

32
00:01:50.377 --> 00:01:52.144
I want to know
what's in that crate.

33
00:01:52.212 --> 00:01:53.740
But we're not
allowed to open it!

34
00:01:53.764 --> 00:01:56.581
I know that!
Go get me a crowbar.

35
00:01:56.650 --> 00:01:58.166
Please. use mine.

36
00:01:58.235 --> 00:02:00.435
I just need it in case. uh...

37
00:02:00.503 --> 00:02:02.804
Fry gets his head
stuck in a pot of honey.

38
00:02:02.873 --> 00:02:05.685
And in the meantime.
if I should happen
to bump

39
00:02:05.709 --> 00:02:07.553
into the crate and open it...

40
00:02:07.577 --> 00:02:08.654
Whoopsie!

41
00:02:10.147 --> 00:02:13.081
Hey. Leela.
Fry got his head
stuck in a pot of honey!

42
00:02:13.149 --> 00:02:14.750
Oh. bother.

43
00:02:14.818 --> 00:02:16.084
Not now!

44
00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:26.128
What is it?
Alcohol? Tobacco?
Firearms?

45
00:02:26.196 --> 00:02:27.362
Firearms!

46
00:02:27.431 --> 00:02:30.282
That's the one I was
secretly hoping for.

47
00:02:33.237 --> 00:02:36.738
I'm okay with most
kinds of violence.
but not gang violence.

48
00:02:36.807 --> 00:02:38.517
Before we deliver these weapons.

49
00:02:38.541 --> 00:02:41.877
we're going to disable them
so they can never be used.

50
00:02:41.945 --> 00:02:43.705
Bender. bend the barrels.

51
00:02:43.747 --> 00:02:44.980
But I love guns!

52
00:02:45.048 --> 00:02:47.043
Then pretend they're
little human necks.

53
00:02:47.067 --> 00:02:48.483
What? Let me at 'em!

54
00:03:02.049 --> 00:03:04.289
A lot of ships get
stolen on this planet.

55
00:03:04.351 --> 00:03:07.085
so. Bender.
stay here
and stand guard.

56
00:03:07.154 --> 00:03:10.394
Okay.
I hope I never
see you again.

57
00:03:19.015 --> 00:03:21.983
Uh. I don't like
the looks of this
gang-infested neighborhood.

58
00:03:22.052 --> 00:03:23.751
There might be spiders!

59
00:03:23.820 --> 00:03:25.298
We must have made a wrong turn.

60
00:03:25.322 --> 00:03:27.334
We should have reached
Blip turf by now.

61
00:03:27.358 --> 00:03:29.524
You think we walked
straight out of Blipton?

62
00:03:29.593 --> 00:03:31.192
Wait. there's some Blips.

63
00:03:32.729 --> 00:03:36.114
Those aren't Blips!
They're Cruds!
They have the red on the left.

64
00:03:36.183 --> 00:03:38.143
Oh. no!
What should we do?

65
00:03:39.119 --> 00:03:42.470
Leela. this is no time
to show me your boobs!

66
00:03:42.539 --> 00:03:44.606
Turn your jersey inside out.

67
00:03:44.675 --> 00:03:46.491
Oh!

68
00:03:46.559 --> 00:03:47.759
Show me again.

69
00:03:51.298 --> 00:03:53.565
Yo. what you doing on our turf?

70
00:03:53.634 --> 00:03:56.729
Chill. dawg.
Ain't no thang.
We Cruds.

71
00:03:56.753 --> 00:03:59.086
Well. we Blips and we over here.

72
00:04:01.357 --> 00:04:04.287
We put up that mirror
'cause this is
a blind intersection.

73
00:04:04.311 --> 00:04:07.295
It's considerably reduced
the number of accidents.

74
00:04:07.364 --> 00:04:09.664
It don't do nothing
for the murder rate. though.

75
00:04:09.733 --> 00:04:13.117
Now get down on your knees
so we can blow
your Crud brains out!

76
00:04:14.888 --> 00:04:17.233
Um.
Leela. remember when
we were trying to guess

77
00:04:17.257 --> 00:04:19.335
what would happen
if someone stuck
a gun in my face.

78
00:04:19.359 --> 00:04:21.638
and you said
I'd probably
crap my pants?

79
00:04:21.662 --> 00:04:23.377
Well...
Excuse me. sir?

80
00:04:23.446 --> 00:04:25.847
We're not actually
Blips or Cruds.

81
00:04:25.916 --> 00:04:28.433
We're delivery people.
here to deliver this crate.

82
00:04:28.502 --> 00:04:32.453
So if everything
seems to be in order.
we'll be on our way. a'ight?

83
00:04:32.523 --> 00:04:34.789
Oh. it's far from a'ight.

84
00:04:34.858 --> 00:04:37.993
Now. hold up!
It's a'ight. all right?

85
00:04:38.061 --> 00:04:40.461
It's a Crud and he's got a gun!

86
00:04:42.833 --> 00:04:45.545
Yo. you just shot
your own reflection
in the mirror.

87
00:04:45.569 --> 00:04:47.001
It was self-defense.

88
00:04:47.070 --> 00:04:49.604
We are the Cruds.
but we're over here.

89
00:04:49.673 --> 00:04:51.939
And don't shoot.
That crate
is a gift from us.

90
00:04:52.008 --> 00:04:53.136
What?
Huh?

91
00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:54.442
For real?

92
00:04:54.511 --> 00:04:56.722
There's been
enough violence
on these streets.

93
00:04:56.746 --> 00:04:59.158
Too many lives
and mirrors have
been shattered.

94
00:04:59.182 --> 00:05:02.984
So. yo. we sent you
a crate of weapons
as a sign of trust.

95
00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:06.805
Together. we can use
them to rid our streets
of the real enemy.

96
00:05:06.873 --> 00:05:08.139
giant spiders.

97
00:05:08.208 --> 00:05:09.248
I knew it!

98
00:05:09.292 --> 00:05:11.192
Man. that's a nice gesture.

99
00:05:11.261 --> 00:05:13.294
We accept your offer of peace.

100
00:05:13.363 --> 00:05:17.049
Let's just have
a look at these
top-quality weapons.

101
00:05:17.101 --> 00:05:19.801
I'll test it out on that
innocent bystander.

102
00:05:19.870 --> 00:05:21.002
Ow!

103
00:05:21.071 --> 00:05:23.438
Yo. you just shot
yourself again!

104
00:05:23.506 --> 00:05:25.117
It's a trick!
Get 'em!

105
00:05:39.323 --> 00:05:41.689
Look. let's just
agree that gang violence

106
00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:44.392
is an important issue
with no easy answers.

107
00:05:44.461 --> 00:05:45.693
Okay.

108
00:05:45.762 --> 00:05:48.596
Anyway.
the ship's still here.
And nothing was stolen.

109
00:05:48.665 --> 00:05:49.897
Yeah. it was.

110
00:05:51.385 --> 00:05:52.684
I got bot-jacked!

111
00:05:53.954 --> 00:05:56.654
All I have left is my cigar.

112
00:05:56.723 --> 00:05:58.890
Wait...

113
00:06:04.798 --> 00:06:07.382
They stole everything
except my mouth and eyes.

114
00:06:07.451 --> 00:06:10.251
I guess they didn't like
all my screaming and winking.

115
00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:13.087
It's just lucky Bender
had a RoJack installed.

116
00:06:13.156 --> 00:06:15.973
When I activate it.
the police should be
able to locate him.

117
00:06:18.862 --> 00:06:21.345
<i>Locating. Locating.</i>

118
00:06:21.414 --> 00:06:22.647
<i>Located.</i>

119
00:06:27.755 --> 00:06:29.588
It's a robot chop shop.

120
00:06:29.656 --> 00:06:32.623
That's some primordial evil.

121
00:06:32.692 --> 00:06:35.660
This skell here
buys stolen robots.
strips 'em down.

122
00:06:35.728 --> 00:06:37.495
and sells the parts
all over the galaxy.

123
00:06:38.948 --> 00:06:41.644
Okay.
I'm getting a signal
from Bender's RoJack.

124
00:06:43.219 --> 00:06:45.331
Nah. it's just a piece of junk.

125
00:06:45.355 --> 00:06:47.989
That's not junk!
That's Bender's head!

126
00:06:48.075 --> 00:06:50.241
My head?
Slap me upside it!

127
00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:52.861
Ah! Home. sweet head.

128
00:06:52.929 --> 00:06:54.880
That's it?
Where's the rest of him?

129
00:06:54.948 --> 00:06:56.547
All other parts sold.

130
00:06:56.616 --> 00:07:00.835
But I have list of buyers.
You drop charges.
I give you list.

131
00:07:00.904 --> 00:07:03.783
No dice.
Justice don't
work that way.

132
00:07:03.807 --> 00:07:05.006
Wait. Wait.

133
00:07:05.075 --> 00:07:08.159
What if I throw in
giant robot head
for nice officer?

134
00:07:08.729 --> 00:07:09.994
Hmm.

135
00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:13.042
Thanks for all
your help. officer!

136
00:07:13.066 --> 00:07:15.967
My pleasure.

137
00:07:16.035 --> 00:07:18.847
Boy. Bender.
you sure were
chock full of parts.

138
00:07:18.871 --> 00:07:21.016
I didn't even know
you had a wishbone.

139
00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:22.891
I had a lot of magic things.

140
00:07:22.976 --> 00:07:24.859
And we'll never
get them all back.

141
00:07:24.928 --> 00:07:26.394
Oh. sure we will.

142
00:07:26.462 --> 00:07:28.229
If we live a really long time.

143
00:07:28.298 --> 00:07:29.981
Let's get started.

144
00:07:44.664 --> 00:07:46.063
Come in. come in.

145
00:07:46.133 --> 00:07:48.228
Close the door.
You're letting
the smut out.

146
00:07:48.252 --> 00:07:49.951
All right. buddy.

147
00:07:50.019 --> 00:07:52.699
We know for a fact
that you received
a stolen item.

148
00:07:52.756 --> 00:07:55.156
A certain sensitive
part of my anatomy.

149
00:07:56.092 --> 00:07:57.453
What. you mean your antenna?

150
00:07:57.477 --> 00:07:59.344
Shh!
Watch your language.

151
00:07:59.412 --> 00:08:01.229
This ain't a church. lady.

152
00:08:01.298 --> 00:08:03.047
Except for tax purposes.

153
00:08:03.116 --> 00:08:04.460
Anyway. I can't help you.

154
00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:07.229
One of my customers
already bought
your friend's antenna.

155
00:08:07.253 --> 00:08:09.637
Oh. excuse me. robo-dong.

156
00:08:09.705 --> 00:08:11.339
Who was it?
Can you give us a name?

157
00:08:11.408 --> 00:08:15.660
Certainly not.
I could never betray
a customer's privacy.

158
00:08:15.729 --> 00:08:17.889
All I can give you is this
naked picture of him

159
00:08:17.914 --> 00:08:19.564
taken from my toilet cam.

160
00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:25.620
I'll get right
to the point. senator.

161
00:08:25.689 --> 00:08:29.857
You purchased
our friend's.
ahem. antenna.

162
00:08:29.926 --> 00:08:31.008
We'd like it back.

163
00:08:31.077 --> 00:08:33.861
- You may have it.
- I'm through with it.

164
00:08:33.930 --> 00:08:37.165
It has done everything
and everyone imaginable.

165
00:08:37.234 --> 00:08:39.462
You may want to
get it disinfected.

166
00:08:39.486 --> 00:08:40.518
Can do.

167
00:08:54.951 --> 00:08:57.552
Sorry. guys.
I'm gonna have
to confiscate your keg.

168
00:08:57.621 --> 00:08:59.120
It's my body.

169
00:08:59.189 --> 00:09:01.956
Oh. come on. Bender!
Can you at least
wait till it's empty?

170
00:09:02.042 --> 00:09:05.610
Fair enough.
Fry. beer me.

171
00:09:05.679 --> 00:09:09.180
Glug. glug. glug. glug.
glug. glug. glug. glug!

172
00:09:10.116 --> 00:09:11.148
Ah!

173
00:09:11.217 --> 00:09:12.333
It's empty!

174
00:09:14.971 --> 00:09:16.938
I'm 40% back. baby!

175
00:09:26.049 --> 00:09:29.083
Sorry. but these robot arms
have brought me
nothing but luck.

176
00:09:29.152 --> 00:09:30.217
With the cards.

177
00:09:33.106 --> 00:09:34.322
And with the ladies.

178
00:09:34.391 --> 00:09:35.973
Whoa! Sir!

179
00:09:36.042 --> 00:09:37.441
But those are my arms!

180
00:09:37.510 --> 00:09:39.611
That's gropey and that's cheaty.

181
00:09:39.679 --> 00:09:40.712
Cheaty?

182
00:09:44.067 --> 00:09:45.867
Now. gentlemen.
I'm sure we can...

183
00:09:48.371 --> 00:09:51.206
Well. then. I'll just
collect my winnings
and be on my...

184
00:09:51.274 --> 00:09:52.307
Oh!

185
00:09:55.511 --> 00:09:56.811
Much obliged.

186
00:10:01.251 --> 00:10:05.020
All right. Tinny.
your double leg
transplant is complete.

187
00:10:05.088 --> 00:10:07.328
What do you say
you give 'em a try?

188
00:10:13.112 --> 00:10:15.647
It's a miracle!
I can walk!

189
00:10:16.883 --> 00:10:19.283
No more crutch or withered leg!

190
00:10:19.352 --> 00:10:22.470
Someone's sure to adopt me now!

191
00:10:22.539 --> 00:10:25.735
Well. Bender. I guess
you won't be getting
your legs back.

192
00:10:25.759 --> 00:10:29.861
But your sacrifice
will let an innocent child
live a full and happy life.

193
00:10:32.999 --> 00:10:34.594
I'm sorry.
You were saying
something?

194
00:10:34.618 --> 00:10:38.786
Oh. crumb.
I guess it's back
to the cart for me.

195
00:10:41.641 --> 00:10:43.608
Ooh! Nice cart.

196
00:10:47.297 --> 00:10:49.342
Hey. this thing's pretty smooth.

197
00:10:49.366 --> 00:10:51.606
But I still prefer walking.

198
00:10:52.836 --> 00:10:55.686
Well. we did it.
We got all
Bender's parts back.

199
00:10:55.755 --> 00:10:57.288
Wrong as always. Fry!

200
00:10:57.357 --> 00:11:00.436
I'm still missing
the shiniest
metal piece of all.

201
00:11:00.460 --> 00:11:01.520
Your thyroid?

202
00:11:01.544 --> 00:11:04.212
No! I'm talking
about my ass!

203
00:11:04.281 --> 00:11:06.847
Huh! I never even
knew you had an ass.

204
00:11:09.402 --> 00:11:13.104
Hmm. According to this.
it shipped out
on a freighter

205
00:11:13.173 --> 00:11:14.839
from South Street Spaceport.

206
00:11:18.194 --> 00:11:22.263
Oh. yes.
I remember that ass.
Let's see.

207
00:11:22.332 --> 00:11:25.833
Oh. God. no!
It was on board
the <i>Floatwell!</i>

208
00:11:25.902 --> 00:11:29.704
The ship
that sank in that
horrible space storm?

209
00:11:29.773 --> 00:11:33.391
Yes. I'm afraid
your friend's derriere
is lost forever

210
00:11:33.460 --> 00:11:35.860
in the depths of
the Sargaseous Sea.

211
00:11:35.928 --> 00:11:39.146
My ass!
Sweet love of my life!

212
00:11:39.215 --> 00:11:42.767
Several hundred
people died. too.
including my wife.

213
00:11:42.835 --> 00:11:44.952
My ass!

214
00:11:45.021 --> 00:11:47.950
I'm sorry. buddy.
Maybe we can
get you a new one.

215
00:11:47.974 --> 00:11:49.240
Never!

216
00:11:49.309 --> 00:11:51.493
My ass is my soul mate.

217
00:11:51.561 --> 00:11:53.639
It even has its own hind-brain.

218
00:11:53.663 --> 00:11:55.864
Really?
Your butt can think?

219
00:11:55.932 --> 00:11:57.898
No.
But it can feel.

220
00:11:57.967 --> 00:12:00.801
And right now.
it's hind-heartbroken!

221
00:12:00.870 --> 00:12:03.955
Just like me!

222
00:12:04.023 --> 00:12:08.125
Wow. Bender.
This is really important
to you. isn't it?

223
00:12:08.194 --> 00:12:10.027
Uh-huh!

224
00:12:10.097 --> 00:12:12.363
Okay. we're gonna
find that shipwreck

225
00:12:12.432 --> 00:12:14.666
and get you your backside back.

226
00:12:16.620 --> 00:12:17.952
Okay. let's go.

227
00:12:32.068 --> 00:12:34.035
The ship carrying
Bender's heinie sank

228
00:12:34.104 --> 00:12:36.738
in the treacherous gases
of the Sargaseous Sea.

229
00:12:36.806 --> 00:12:37.972
Once we locate the wreck...

230
00:12:38.041 --> 00:12:40.458
Asteroids!

231
00:12:46.382 --> 00:12:48.299
Curse this interstellar fog.

232
00:12:48.367 --> 00:12:51.185
Why isn't there a lighthouse
to guide us away
from the rocks?

233
00:12:51.254 --> 00:12:53.771
I don't know.
but look out for
that lighthouse!

234
00:13:05.101 --> 00:13:06.863
So you're alive. are ye?

235
00:13:06.887 --> 00:13:10.721
Ugh! I suppose
you'll be wanting to
keep your tooth fillin's.

236
00:13:10.791 --> 00:13:11.972
Are ye hurt?

237
00:13:12.041 --> 00:13:14.475
No. but we could use a hug.

238
00:13:15.345 --> 00:13:17.111
Better come inside then.

239
00:13:20.517 --> 00:13:22.016
Name's Tarquin.

240
00:13:22.085 --> 00:13:24.947
Been alone here.
tending this light
longer'n I can remember.

241
00:13:26.289 --> 00:13:28.072
That'll be my cup-a-soup.

242
00:13:28.141 --> 00:13:31.142
It's been microwavin'
longer'n I can remember.

243
00:13:31.211 --> 00:13:32.777
This is a dangerous coast.

244
00:13:32.845 --> 00:13:35.165
We didn't see your light
until it was too late.

245
00:13:35.214 --> 00:13:37.931
No beam can pierce
that devilish mist.

246
00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:39.600
Shipwrecks be so common.

247
00:13:39.669 --> 00:13:42.370
I make a good livin'
out of whatever
washes ashore.

248
00:13:42.438 --> 00:13:44.856
Found me a whole
blue man group once.

249
00:13:44.924 --> 00:13:46.407
So you have two jobs?

250
00:13:46.476 --> 00:13:50.311
More.
I also salvage the wrecks
with my bathysphere.

251
00:13:50.396 --> 00:13:54.498
and I'm a butcher.
if you like blue meat.

252
00:13:54.567 --> 00:13:57.079
Sounds good.
but about that
bathysphere.

253
00:13:57.103 --> 00:13:59.181
We want to salvage
a cargo ship that sank

254
00:13:59.205 --> 00:14:00.950
carrying this robot's rear end.

255
00:14:00.974 --> 00:14:04.558
Aye. I'll help ye
for a cut of the booty.

256
00:14:04.627 --> 00:14:07.227
Now. when you say
a cut of the booty...

257
00:14:07.296 --> 00:14:10.281
I mean
a percentage of the value
of the recovered goods.

258
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:11.783
Now be gettin' some rest.

259
00:14:11.851 --> 00:14:14.211
The booty call is at daybreak.

260
00:15:09.342 --> 00:15:11.809
<i>Those sound like
one-eyed corpse screams.</i>

261
00:15:11.877 --> 00:15:14.679
Oh. how I wish I was
down there with ye.

262
00:15:17.516 --> 00:15:19.227
Let's not forget
that this shipwreck

263
00:15:19.251 --> 00:15:23.070
is also
the final resting place
of this brave captain.

264
00:15:23.139 --> 00:15:25.039
Place your bets.
Whee!

265
00:15:34.467 --> 00:15:38.469
That's it.
I'm sure. I can tell by
the words on the crate!

266
00:15:40.340 --> 00:15:43.574
Oh. my beloved.
You complete me.

267
00:15:52.869 --> 00:15:55.603
Hurry on inside now.
Storm's a-brewin'.

268
00:15:55.671 --> 00:15:57.572
I can feel it in my
weather channel app.

269
00:16:01.461 --> 00:16:04.746
Soon the sea will be
belchin' her dead
upon the shore.

270
00:16:04.814 --> 00:16:07.681
If you like your
shoes unmatched and
with feet still in 'em.

271
00:16:07.751 --> 00:16:09.016
this is your night.

272
00:16:14.390 --> 00:16:16.290
Can't you make
the beacon
any brighter?

273
00:16:16.359 --> 00:16:19.679
Nay. 'tis already
the brightest object
in the known universe.

274
00:16:19.729 --> 00:16:23.431
and even so. it can't
be seen three feet away
in a storm like this.

275
00:16:30.473 --> 00:16:32.083
I thought we were
near the rocks.

276
00:16:32.107 --> 00:16:33.419
but I don't see the lighthouse.

277
00:16:33.443 --> 00:16:36.561
so everything is
fine and we can relax.

278
00:16:36.629 --> 00:16:40.231
<i>All hands on deck for mojitos.</i>

279
00:16:40.299 --> 00:16:43.601
The important thing is.
I got my final piece back.

280
00:16:43.653 --> 00:16:47.305
Hey. Fry. take a picture
of me biting my own
shiny metal ass.

281
00:16:47.373 --> 00:16:48.706
I'd be honored.

282
00:16:58.551 --> 00:16:59.683
Ah!

283
00:16:59.752 --> 00:17:02.952
You muddled
the mint well.
Alejandro.

284
00:17:06.142 --> 00:17:08.582
The lighthouse!
Dead ahead!
Aye!

285
00:17:14.967 --> 00:17:17.317
Well. I'm sure
Bender's fanny is tired.

286
00:17:17.386 --> 00:17:19.487
As soon
as this storm passes.
let's be on our way.

287
00:17:21.274 --> 00:17:25.092
Sargaseous lighthouse.
this is the <i>S.S.</i>
<i>Miami Muy Caliente.</i>

288
00:17:25.161 --> 00:17:27.094
Thank you for
your glorious beacon.

289
00:17:27.163 --> 00:17:30.531
It saved our lives
and our Saturday night.

290
00:17:30.600 --> 00:17:31.632
<i>Adios.</i>

291
00:17:35.121 --> 00:17:36.487
Your aft-plate.

292
00:17:36.556 --> 00:17:39.791
Its fiery gleam saved a ship
full of South Beach swabbies.

293
00:17:39.859 --> 00:17:41.893
Well. I do polish it every day.

294
00:17:41.961 --> 00:17:43.839
and I sleep in a chamois diaper.

295
00:17:43.863 --> 00:17:47.465
It's 100 times more
reflective than the mirror
in my beacon.

296
00:17:47.534 --> 00:17:49.684
Might I keep it
for the lighthouse?

297
00:17:49.769 --> 00:17:51.168
What? No!

298
00:17:51.237 --> 00:17:54.272
But. Bender.
your buttocks
could save lives.

299
00:17:54.340 --> 00:17:55.672
I hate lives!

300
00:17:55.725 --> 00:17:57.858
These are sailors' lives.
Bender.

301
00:17:57.927 --> 00:18:01.628
Think of the untold cursing
that would be lost
to future generations.

302
00:18:01.698 --> 00:18:03.380
Could you live with that?

303
00:18:05.801 --> 00:18:10.071
You know the answer.
you scurvy bastard!

304
00:18:10.139 --> 00:18:14.308
Maybe I have been selfish.
hiding my ass under a bushel.

305
00:18:14.377 --> 00:18:18.362
Perhaps.
like all great men.
my ass has a destiny.

306
00:18:18.431 --> 00:18:21.765
And if it does.
I can't stand in its way.

307
00:19:00.390 --> 00:19:04.058
Bender. come join us.
We're watching <i>Rear Window.</i>

308
00:19:04.126 --> 00:19:07.094
I used to stick my
rear out the window.

309
00:19:07.163 --> 00:19:10.231
If you prefer.
we could watch
<i>Behind the Music.</i>

310
00:19:10.299 --> 00:19:12.550
My behind used to make music.

311
00:19:12.618 --> 00:19:14.118
<i>Backdraft</i> is on.

312
00:19:14.186 --> 00:19:16.436
Even my ass wouldn't watch that.

313
00:19:16.505 --> 00:19:19.640
Bender. I'm proud of you
for the sacrifice you made.

314
00:19:19.709 --> 00:19:23.077
Try and find solace
in the fact that
somewhere out there.

315
00:19:23.145 --> 00:19:25.145
your keister is doing good.

316
00:19:32.137 --> 00:19:35.606
Well. my shiny friend.
yer days of carousin'
are over.

317
00:19:35.675 --> 00:19:40.027
But yer nights of endless.
monotonous rotatin'
have just begun.

318
00:19:40.096 --> 00:19:43.364
Now what say I read
you a nice passage
from the Scripture

319
00:19:43.433 --> 00:19:45.982
to help you forget
yer old master?

320
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:55.359
"In the sanctuary. he made
two cherubim of olive-wood.

321
00:19:55.427 --> 00:20:00.030
"each 10 cubits high
and one wing measured
five cubits.

322
00:20:00.099 --> 00:20:03.884
"And the other wing measured
five cubits from the tip..."

323
00:20:14.363 --> 00:20:17.615
Oh. no! Our son Johnny
fell down the gravity well!

324
00:20:23.539 --> 00:20:25.306
Thank you. Assie.

325
00:20:35.601 --> 00:20:37.668
Bender? It's for you.

326
00:20:41.824 --> 00:20:43.507
Assie?

327
00:20:43.575 --> 00:20:46.493
Oh. Assie. you came home!

328
00:20:47.063 --> 00:20:49.329
You came home.
